; Stow the current spindle tool in the carousel (stow-only, no new tool loaded).
; Called from the "STORE TOOL IN SPINDLE" button on the ATC tab.
; Uses T0 M6 via our remap: fatc runs the stow sequence and skips the load phase.

o<store_tool_in_carousel> sub
(PRINT, o<store_tool_in_carousel>)

; #<_current_tool> is the LinuxCNC predefined parameter for tool in spindle (#5400).
; #<tool_in_spindle> is only available inside the M6 remap context (set by change_prolog).
o100 if [#<_current_tool> LE 0]
    (abort, No tool in spindle -- nothing to store)
o100 endif

T0 M6

o<store_tool_in_carousel> endsub

M2
